{"title":"fix(remediation): increase mem-load memory limit to prevent OOMKilled","body":"Root cause: The mem-load container's memory limit (32Mi) is insufficient for the stress command it executes (--vm-bytes 50M), causing OOMKilled when the stress test allocates more memory than the limit allows.

Evidence: Container mem-load resources: limits.memory=32Mi but stress command uses --vm-bytes 50M which exceeds the limit.

Fix: Increased mem-load memory limit from 32Mi to 64Mi to accommodate the 50M stress allocation."}

{"title":"fix(remediation): increase mem-load memory limit to prevent OOMKilled","body":"Root cause: The mem-load sidecar container's 64Mi memory limit is insufficient for the stress tool running with --vm-bytes 50M plus runtime overhead, causing OOMKilled terminations.

Evidence: rollout_status shows ReplicaFailure condition with reason FailedCreate; alert KubeContainerOOMKilled fired for deployment vigil-app; mem-load container has 64Mi limit while stress --vm-bytes 50M consumes additional overhead beyond the allocated bytes.

Fix: Increase mem-load container memory limit from 64Mi to 128Mi."}
